<div class="xar-mod-head"><span class="xar-mod-title"><xar:mlstring>Figlet Administration</xar:mlstring></span></div>
<div class="xar-mod-body">
    <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>
    <div style="padding: 1px;" class="xar-norm-outline">
        <div style="float:right;padding:10px;">
            <xar:if condition="file_exists('modules/mail/xarimages/admin.gif')" >
                <img src="modules/mail/xarimages/admin.gif" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" />
            <xar:else />
                <img src="modules/mail/xarimages/admin_generic.gif" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" />
            </xar:if>
        </div>
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <xar:mlstring>The Figlet module uses a class written by <a href="http://www.thebobo.com/?page=php,figlet#do">Lucas Baltes</a> to transform text to Ascii art.  This module includes a special text transform called transformfig which will take any call to it and transform the text to Ascii art of your choosing.  It also offers a user page to allow any text to be transformed.  Good for use with signatures, etc.</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <xar:mlstring>From the menu, you have one choice. </xar:mlstring>
            <xar:mlstring>"Modify Configuration".  From this menu option, you can update the necessary configuration options, such as the default font to use.</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <xar:mlstring>The Mail Module has no blocks included at this time.</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div class="xar-mod-title xar-norm-outline" style="margin-top: 1em; margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; width: auto; border-style: none none dotted none;">
            <xar:mlstring>Included Hooks</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
        <br />
        <div style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align:left;">
            <xar:mlstring>The figlet modules uses a special case text transform which when called will transform text to ascii art.</xar:mlstring>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
